      • build

        public TemplateConfiguration build()
        Description copied from interface: CommonBuilder
        Creates an instance of the product class. This is usually a new instance, though if the product is stateless, it's possibly a shared object instead of a new one. Builders shouldn't allow calling this method for multiple times (not counting calls that threw exceptions), and should throw IllegalStateException to prevent that.
        Specified by:
        build in interface CommonBuilder<TemplateConfiguration>

      • merge

        public void merge(TemplateConfiguration tc)
        Set all settings in this TemplateConfiguration.Builder that were set in the parameter TemplateConfiguration (or other ParsingAndProcessingConfiguration), possibly overwriting the earlier value in this object. (A setting is said to be set in a ParsingAndProcessingConfiguration if it was explicitly set via a setter method, as opposed to be inherited.)
